# Ship changes to GitHub

When you finish edits the user asked for in **this repository** (`fuze-journal`):

1. Ensure `index.html` (and any other touched files) reflect the requested work.
2. Run `git status` from the repo root, then `git add` for changed paths, `git commit` with a short imperative message describing what changed and why, then `git push` to the tracked default branch (usually `origin/main`).
3. If `git push` fails (auth, network, non-repo workspace), report the exact error and what the user must do; do not claim the push succeeded.
4. Do not skip push for “small” edits — the user expects GitHub to stay in sync whenever they request a change.
